 IRON BOX [UNIX/Internet] n. A special environment set up to trap a CRACKER
logging in over remote or network connections long enough so he can be
traced. May include a specially-gimmicked SHELL restricting the hacker's
movements in unobvious ways, and `bait' files designed to keep him interested
and logged on. see also BACK DOOR, FIREWALL, VENUS FLYTRAP.